column2: Heavy rain last several days.Beaver activity causing water level to rise.  Level up 2-3 inches based on boat dock distance from water.
Lots of rain.  Beaver activity continues.  Most boat docks touching water.  Loons present since ice out.  No signs of nest.
Boater looking for loon nest.  No loon chicks sighted.
Many careless boaters motoring close to shore.  Persons in Kayak probing every inch of shore looking for wildlife.  little regard for waterfowl.
One adult loon spotted.  Some boat activity.

Bottom is 10.25 feet.  No boating activity on lake.  Ice out was on 4/10/2015.  Not certain if this date can be entered online.  No loons this year.  Have had loons past four years.  My guess was the water level changing frequently causing nest failure.  I plan to install 15" pipes through dams next year to regulate water level.
Loon pair not nesting again this year.  lake level more constant due to reduced Beaver activity.
Aquatic plant beds seem larger than usual.  Not invasive Aquatic vegetation.
bottom of lake can be seen.  very clear.
ice out first week of april
Aggressive Eagle activity and or drastic level changes possible reason Round Lake had Loon nesting failure again.
Cool day.  Occasional loon sighted.  Wondering if ANP for loons would be helpful.  Several rentals on lake.  All season folks disturbed waterfowl nesting areas.
